#: ../../O/overrun-screw.rst:5
msgid "overrun screw"
msgstr "overrun screw"

#: ../../O/overrun-screw.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../O/overrun-screw.rst:9
msgid ""
"[C programming] A variety of :ref:`fandango-on-core` produced by scribbling "
"past the end of an array (C implementations typically have no checks for "
"this error). This is relatively benign and easy to spot if the array is "
"static; if it is auto, the result may be to :ref:`smash-the-stack` — often "
"resulting in :ref:`heisenbug`\\s of the most diabolical subtlety. The term "
"overrun screw is used esp. of scribbles beyond the end of arrays allocated "
"with :manpage:`malloc(3)`\\; this typically trashes the allocation header "
"for the next block in the :ref:`arena`\\, producing massive lossage within "
"malloc and often a core dump on the next operation to use "
":manpage:`stdio(3)` or :manpage:`malloc(3)` itself. See :ref:`spam`\\, "
":ref:`overrun`\\; see also :ref:`memory-leak`\\, :ref:`memory-smash`\\, "
":ref:`aliasing-bug`\\, :ref:`precedence-lossage`\\, :ref:`fandango-on-"
"core`\\, :ref:`secondary-damage`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Cプログラミング]配列の末尾を超えて書き込むことで生じる\\ :ref:`fandango-on-core`\\ "
"の一種(C実装は通常この誤りに対するチェックを持たない)。配列が静的なら、これは比較的無害で見つけやすい。自動変数なら、結果として\\ "
":ref:`smash-the-stack`\\ することがあり——しばしば最も悪魔的に微妙な\\ :ref:`heisenbug`\\ "
"を引き起こす。overrun screwという用語は、特に\\ :manpage:`malloc(3)`\\ "
"で割り当てられた配列の末尾を超える書き込みについて使われる。これは典型的には\\ :ref:`arena`\\ "
"内の次のブロックの割り当てヘッダを破壊し、malloc内で大規模なlossageを引き起こし、しばしば\\ :manpage:`stdio(3)`\\ "
"または\\ :manpage:`malloc(3)`\\ 自体を使う次の操作でコアダンプを起こす。\\ :ref:`spam`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`overrun`\\ を参照。\\ :ref:`memory-leak`\\ 、\\ :ref:`memory-smash`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`aliasing-bug`\\ 、\\ :ref:`precedence-lossage`\\ 、\\ :ref:`fandango-on-"
"core`\\ 、\\ :ref:`secondary-damage`\\ も参照。"
